'''Ailill mac Fergusa''' (died 800) was King of South [[Kings of Brega|Brega]] of the Uí Chernaig sept of [[Lagore]] of the [[Síl nÁedo Sláine]] branch of the southern [[Ui Neill]]. He was the son of [[Fergus mac Fogartaig]] (died 751) and brother of [[Máel Dúin mac Fergusa]] (died 785), previous kings.<ref>Mac Niocaill, pg.141</ref> he ruled from 797 to 800.
The annals record that he died from being thrown from a horse.<ref>''Annals of Ulster'', AU 800.4</ref> He is styled ''rex Deisceirt Bregh''-King of South Brega.
